task.summary: Default task
Initialized PyCharm project.
Reformat code.
Derive the moving_average_length in terms of the frame length.
IDE config updates.
Remove unnecessary double transpose of power data.
Refactor code so all functions run on an array of slices in first the time domain, then the frequency domain, to better work with streaming data
Started to reorganize into a structure that can support analyzing streaming data. Code is in a transitional state and will not currently run properly.
Code is now functional. Processes the audio file in pieces of size AUDIO_BUFFER.
Renamed some variables and fixed calculation of FFT interval.
Completed transition to a streaming buffer processing system.
Fix long-term moving average, added high-pass filtering, and modified rolloff frequency to use high-pass filter.
Properly extract the third octave for further analysis.
Display buffer data on plot.
Created framework for generating feature vectors from each time slice of data.
Get the autocorrelation coefficient for the third octave, and set up a framework for feature vector collection and classification.
Fixed buffer size bug.
Added file training and analysis classes.
Load files from the recordings directory for training.
First attempt at training the neural network using annotations for car.wav.
Trained the neural network and tested on sample data.
Realtime classifier.
Fixed realtime processing of microphone input.
Improved algorithm to prevent NaN errors and to subtract the moving average properly.
Graphed improvement seen in output.
Performed some speed optimizations to speed up the calculation of feature vectors, in particular skipping the slow trim_outliers method.
Modified normalization methods, fixed graphical display of analysis results, and switched to more efficient XML-based classifier storage method.
Added null recording files.
Tweaked parameters and fixed autocorrelation coefficient calculation.
More tweaks to parameters.
Compare ratios between pairs of frequency bands instead of their magnitudes directly.
Fixed pairwise ratio calculation.
Added generated noise wav files as null data.
Switched to using pairwise differences in decibels to better represent ratios of power, and take the absolute value when normalizing.
Tweaked some parameters and changed normalization method to a moving threshold set at 2 standard deviations below the mean.
Use a sliding minimum of smoothed values to set the threshold instead of using standard deviations.
Print the result to the console.
Additional tweaks to improve accuracy, and adjusted output thresholds.
Use three hidden layers, and add standard deviation of frequencies in each time slice as a measure of entropy into the feature vector for improved accuracy.
Global high-pass filter at 500 Hz to drop noisy frequencies with wind noise.
Some code for plotting realtime data in realtime, and attempted fixes for the realtime analysis.
Began to implement own FFT code.
Added adapted implementation of FFT code as a FFT class.
Implemented a more proper interface for reading data from the AudioBuffer.
Switched to custom FFT class in FeatureVectorExtractor.analyze.
Inlined some variables for efficiency.
Convert the normalize function to accept a single slice.
Add missing buffer.
Convert zero crossing rate.
Convert rolloff_freq.
Convert slices_bins.
Convert third octave and third octave autocorrelation.
Convert pairwise differences.
Convert magnitude.
Convert stddev.
Remove loop over the one vector.
Remove unused function in AudioBuffer and renamed push_samples to push.
Fixed realtime analyzer.
Extracted FFT sample length calculations into a helper class.
Remove unused nextpow2 function in FeatureVectorExtractor class.
Remove unused list_sum method in FeatureVectorExtractor class.
Remove unused trim_outliers method in FeatureVectorExtractor class.
Remove unused step_length method in FeatureVectorExtractor class.
Convert high_pass_filter method.
Annotated fft run method.
